      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEW TARGET (8) missed by 0.9L first-up at Belmont, though she was very strong late in the race when settling back from a wide draw. She now gets the chance to sit closer today with Parnham replacing the apprentice hoop. Fitter for the fresh run and can turn the tables. QUEEN OF HAWKS (6) bolted in at the trials recently in good order and looks set for a bold showing fresh. She has the speed to roll forward from the draw and jumped favourite in what turned out to be a good form race at the end of last campaign. Can put her best foot forward. MAI ALOHA (7) returned with a bang when beating NEW TARGET first-up at Belmont. She was favourite there, though this sets up a little differently second-up. Pike rides again and it wouldn't surprise to see her repeat the dose. EMPRESS OF INDIA (1) has returned in good order this campaign and can't be discounted in this easier assignment.",
